        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 3:31PM PDT by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Eagle Rock, or near Downtown Los Angeles, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail. Locally heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Griffith Park...
Downtown Los Angeles...
Eagle Rock...
Elysian Park...
Echo Park...
Atwater Village...
Highland Park...
Boyle Heights...
Chinatown...
Los Feliz...
Silverlake...
and Mt. Washington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
